This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with personalized recommendation. It also involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and deep-semantic modeling, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the integration of multiple sources of information, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of tags, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
